The paper deals with matrix completion and collaborative filtering, which are topics commonly studied in the machine learning community. The use of trace-norm regularization is also a common technique in this field. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with recommendation systems, which falls under the scope of information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of non-uniform sampling is a statistical problem, which could be classified under data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) or statistics (cs.SI).
